This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video deblurring, which is a common problem in computer vision. Additionally, the use of optical flow estimation and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) are common techniques in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category as video deblurring is a common problem in multimedia processing. 

The paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a Spatio-Temporal Filter Adaptive Network (STFAN) which is a type of neural network. 

The paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes a new method for video deblurring which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 

The paper may belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) category as video deblurring is a common problem in computer graphics, and the proposed method involves the use of filters and convolutional layers which are commonly used in computer graphics.
